		{
			"img": "https://assets.forge-vtt.com/bazaar/systems/pf2e/assets/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
			"name": "Head Regrowth",
			"sort": 375000,
			"system": {
				"actionType": {
					"value": "passive"
				},
				"actions": {
					"value": null
				},
				"category": "defensive",
				"description": {
					"value": "<p>Aleadar has seven heads. A creature can attempt to sever one of Adear's heads by specifically targeting it and dealing damage equal to the head's Hit Points. A head that is not completely severed returns to full Hit Points at the end of any creature's turn. Aleadar can regrow a severed head using Hydra Regeneration. A creature can prevent this regrowth by dealing acid or good damage to the stump, cauterizing it. Single-target acid or good effects need to be targeted at a specific stump, but effects that deal splash damage or affect areas covering the hydra's whole space cauterize all stumps if they deal acid or good damage. If the attack that severs a head deals any acid or good damage, the stump is cauterized instantly. If all seven heads are cauterized, Aleadar dies.</p><hr /><p><strong>Hydra Head</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Hit Points</strong> 39</li><li><strong>Immunities</strong> Area Damage</li><li><strong>Weaknesses</strong> Slashing 8</li></ul><p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-effects.Item.uZJOdounIHaFDC1t]{Effect: Hydra Heads}</p>",
					"gm": ""
				},
