				},
				"category": "offensive",
				"description": {
					"value": "<p>Aleadar attacks a single target with its heads, overwhelming its foe with multiple attacks and leaving almost nowhere to dodge. Aleadar Strikes with its fangs. On a successful attack, the hydra deals damage from its fangs Strike to the target, plus an additional [[/r 1d6]] damage for every head it has beyond the first. On a failure (but not a critical failure), the hydra deals the damage from one fangs Strike to the target creature. This Strike counts as a number of attacks equal to the number of heads the hydra has toward the hydra's multiple attack penalty.</p>",
